{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"enum"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"DiskInjector"}],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Overview","anchor":"overview","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Before the VM boots, ","type":"text"},{"code":"DiskInjector","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" mounts the guest disk image on the host,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"writes a standard macOS LaunchDaemon plist and the user’s script to the data","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"volume, then unmounts. When the VM boots, ","type":"text"},{"code":"launchd","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" picks up the daemon and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"executes the script automatically — no SSH, no agent, no network required.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This uses Apple’s ","type":"text"},{"code":"hdiutil","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" (ships with macOS) to attach APFS disk images","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and writes only to the data volume (never the Signed System Volume).","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Usage","anchor":"Usage","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"codeListing","code":["let scriptURL = URL(fileURLWithPath: \"\/path\/to\/setup.sh\")","let bundle = try VirtualMachineBundle.load(from: bundleURL)","try DiskInjector.inject(script: scriptURL, into: bundle)"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"How It Works","anchor":"How-It-Works"},{"type":"orderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Attaches the guest’s "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"disk.img"},{"type":"text","text":" using "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"hdiutil"},{"type":"text","text":" without mounting"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(to discover the device node)."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Finds and mounts the APFS data volume from the attached disk.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Writes the user’s script to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\/usr\/local\/bin\/spooktacular-user-data.sh"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"on the data volume."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Writes a LaunchDaemon plist to "},{"code":"\/Library\/LaunchDaemons\/","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" that tells"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"launchd","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" to run the script at boot."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Detaches the disk image so the VM can boot cleanly."}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Thread-Safety","text":"Thread Safety"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"All methods are synchronous and use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Process"},{"type":"text","text":" to invoke "},{"code":"hdiutil","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Call from a background thread if needed to avoid blocking the main thread."}]}]}],"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Enumeration","modules":[{"name":"SpooktacularKit"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"DiskInjector","kind":"identifier"}],"externalID":"s:15SpooktacularKit12DiskInjectorO","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"enum"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"DiskInjector"}],"title":"DiskInjector","symbolKind":"enum","role":"symbol"},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/DiskInjector","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"abstract":[{"text":"Injects a user-data script into a VM’s guest disk as a macOS LaunchDaemon.","type":"text"}],"topicSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKi